Build a simple, clean, frontend-only To-Do web application using plain HTML, CSS, and JavaScript (no frameworks).

The app should be designed to be deployed on GitHub Pages, so it must not rely on any backend, server, or external database.

Core Requirements:
- Single-page application
- Add a new to-do item
- Mark a to-do item as complete/incomplete
- Delete a to-do item
- Persist all to-dos using localStorage so they remain after page refresh
- Input field + "Add" button
- Display list of tasks below the input

UI/UX Requirements:
- Clean, modern design (centered container)
- Responsive layout (mobile + desktop)
- Subtle hover effects on buttons
- Completed tasks should be visually distinct (e.g., strikethrough + faded)
- Smooth transitions (CSS preferred)

Feature Enhancements (include these):
1. Filter buttons:
   - All
   - Active
   - Completed

2. Clear completed tasks button

3. Task counter:
   - Show number of active (incomplete) tasks remaining

4. Edit task:
   - Allow user to click a task and edit its text inline

5. Keyboard support:
   - Press "Enter" to add a task

6. LocalStorage structure:
   - Store tasks as an array of objects:
     {
       id: string,
       text: string,
       completed: boolean
     }

Code Requirements:
- Use clean, readable JavaScript (no libraries)
- Separate logic clearly (DOM handling, storage, rendering)
- Comment important sections for learning purposes
- Use semantic HTML
- Keep everything in 3 files:
  - index.html
  - styles.css
  - app.js

Bonus (if easy to include):
- Dark mode toggle (persisted in localStorage)
- Simple animation when adding/removing tasks

Output:
- Provide complete code for all files
- Ensure it works by simply opening index.html in a browser
- Ensure compatibility with GitHub Pages deployment